  "description": [
    "ASKS FOR FEDERAL CHILD MlBUREAU National Committee Conference Adjourns After Draft my nesuiuiiuii HEARS ARGUMENTS FOR THE PALMEROWEN BILL Speakers Declare at Closing Session for Model Code Unifying State Laws on the Subject The eleventh annual conference on child labor which has been in session at the New Willard Hotel this week under the auspices of the national child labor committee adjourned last night after listening to a number of addresses in favor of the Palmer Owen child labor bill now pending in Congress The present laws for children were characterized by Edward X Clopper of New York secretary of the national child labor committee for the northern states as rambling chaotic extreme archaic contradictory incomplete and obsolete The conference drafted and referred to the committees trustees a resolution asking the creation of a federal child labor bureau to prepare a model code unifying state laws on the subject Before doing so Mr Clopper proposed a childrens charter embracing all the accepted standards of KiU nolfori lift coirl Codification Strongly Urged Nearly every state in the Union has today on its statute books a great mass of legislation for the welfare of children he said Some of it is archaic"
  ],
